    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Good observation, but what we actually updated git in some other docker images to make sure it works with `git submodule --reference` (which is more efficient because it doesn't end up cloning from all the submodules from github).\r\n\r\nAnother problem is that the code for cloning submodule with the reference repo is in more places than just the file you are changing and I'd prefer to have everything behave the same if possible.\r\n\r\nThe fix in https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/9109/files has helped with centos 6.x, manylinux seems to be based on centos 5.11 so modifications might be necessary.\r\nhttps://github.com/pypa/manylinux/blob/master/docker/Dockerfile-x86_64"
  },
